The paper deals with unsupervised person re-identification, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a deep model for soft multilabel learning, which involves learning a real-valued label likelihood vector for each unlabeled person. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper evaluates the proposed model on two datasets, Market-1501 and DukeMTMC-reID, which are related to multimedia and computer vision, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for hard negative mining, which is a technique used in cryptography and security. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
